Learning_Other_Unit_TypeObject.description: Display information used to describe an instance of an object. This 'optional' information is for outbound descriptive purposes only and is not processed on inbound Workday Web Services requests.

Learning_Other_Unit_TypeObjectID.description: The unique identifier type. Each "ID" for an instance of an object contains a type and a value. A single instance of an object can have multiple "ID" but only a single "ID" per "type".  Some "types" require a reference to a parent instance.

Learning_Other_Unit_TypeObject.description: Contains a unique identifier for an instance of an object.

description: Identifies other unit types using unique references for updates. Leave blank when adding other unit types. For update, the ID corresponds to other unit type name.

Learning_Other_Unit_Type_Data.description: Unique name of the other unit type.

validation.validation: Learning Other Unit Type Name must be Unique.

Learning_Other_Unit_Type_Data.description: Indicates whether the course is inactive.
